## Contract

Bookmarks are saved URLs with a required URL, required non-empty title, optional
description, optional folder assignment, and ISO timestamp metadata.

## API

- `POST /bookmarks` creates a bookmark and returns `201` with the created row.
- `GET /bookmarks` returns `200` with all bookmarks as an array.
- `GET /bookmarks/:id` returns `200` with one bookmark or `404`.
- `PUT /bookmarks/:id` updates supplied bookmark fields and returns `200` with
  the updated row or `404`.
- `DELETE /bookmarks/:id` deletes a bookmark and returns `204` or `404`.
- `POST /folders` creates a folder and returns `201` with the created row.
- `GET /folders` returns `200` with all folders as an array.
- `GET /folders/:id` returns `200` with one folder plus its bookmarks or `404`.
- `PUT /folders/:id` updates the folder name and returns `200` or `404`.
- `DELETE /folders/:id` deletes the folder and returns `204` or `404`.

## Validation

- `url` is required for create and must be a valid URL when supplied.
- `title` is required for create and must be a non-empty string when supplied.
- `description` is optional and stored as `null` when omitted.
- `folder_id` is optional for bookmark create and update, may be `null`, and
  must reference an existing folder when supplied.
- Folder `name` is required and must be a non-empty string.

## Storage

Bookmarks persist in `data.db` in the `bookmarks` table. Folders persist in the
`folders` table. Bookmark rows include a nullable `folder_id`; deleting a folder
sets matching bookmarks' `folder_id` to `null` instead of deleting bookmarks.
