## Status

implemented

## Lane

normal

## Product Contract

The API persists folders in SQLite and lets bookmarks optionally belong to one
folder. Folder deletion leaves bookmarks intact and clears their `folder_id`.
Bookmark create and update requests reject a non-existent `folder_id` with
`400`.

## Relevant Product Docs

- `PRODUCT_SPEC.md`

## Acceptance Criteria

- `POST /folders` creates a folder and returns `201`.
- `GET /folders` returns all folders as an array.
- `GET /folders/:id` returns the folder plus its bookmarks or `404`.
- `PUT /folders/:id` updates the folder name or returns `404`.
- `DELETE /folders/:id` deletes the folder with `204` or returns `404`.
- Bookmarks can be created and updated with `folder_id`.
- Deleting a folder nullifies matching bookmark `folder_id` values.
- Non-existent or invalid `folder_id` values return `400`.
- Existing bookmark CRUD endpoints continue to work.

## Design Notes

- Commands: create, update, delete folder rows; create and update bookmark
  folder assignment.
- Queries: list folders, fetch folder with bookmarks, list/read bookmarks with
  `folder_id`.
- API: REST endpoints under `/folders`; `folder_id` accepted by bookmark create
  and update endpoints.
- Tables: `folders`; `bookmarks.folder_id` nullable foreign key.
- Domain rules: folder `name` is required and non-empty; folder deletion
  unfolders bookmarks instead of deleting them.
- UI surfaces: none.

## Validation

| Layer | Expected proof |
| --- | --- |
| Unit | TypeScript build |
| Integration | HTTP requests for folder CRUD, bookmark folder assignment, invalid `folder_id`, and delete nullification |
| E2E | Not required for API-only slice |
| Platform | SQLite `data.db` contains `folders` table and `bookmarks.folder_id` |
| Release | Not required |

## Harness Delta

No harness behavior changes expected.

## Evidence

- `npm run build` passed.
- Manual HTTP checks passed on port 3100 for health, folder create/list/read
  with bookmarks/update/delete, bookmark create with `folder_id`, bookmark
  create/update invalid `folder_id` failures, delete nullification, and
  bookmark create/list regression.
- `sqlite3 data.db ".schema folders"` verified the `folders` table.
- `sqlite3 data.db ".schema bookmarks"` verified `bookmarks.folder_id`.
- `npm test` currently exits with code 1 because no Vitest test files exist.
